name: Amazon SQS Message Start Event Connector

groups.label: Use next attribute names for activation condition

properties.label: Authentication
properties.description: Specify AWS authentication strategy. Learn more at the documentation page

properties.label: Access key
properties.description: Provide AWS IAM access key that has permission to read from desired SQS

properties.label: Secret key
properties.description: Provide AWS IAM secret key that has permission to read from desired SQS

properties.label: Queue URL
properties.description: Specify the URL of the SQS queue where you would like to subscribe to

pattern.message: Must be an queue URL or ARN

properties.label: Region
properties.description: Specify the AWS region of your queue

properties.label: Polling wait time
properties.description: The duration (in seconds) for which the call waits for a message to arrive in the queue before returning. See documentation for details

pattern.message: Must be >= 0 and <= 20 or a FEEL expression

properties.label: Attribute names
properties.description: Array of queue attribute names. See documentation for details

properties.label: Message attribute names
properties.description: Array of message attribute names. See documentation for details

properties.label: Message ID expression
properties.description: Expression to extract unique identifier of a message

properties.label: Activation condition
properties.description: Condition under which the connector triggers. Leave empty to catch all events

properties.label: Correlation required
properties.description: Indicates whether correlation is required. This is needed for event-based subprocess message start events

properties.label: Correlation key (process)
properties.description: Sets up the correlation key from process variables

properties.label: Correlation key (payload)
properties.description: Extracts the correlation key from the incoming message payload

properties.label: Result variable
properties.description: Name of variable to store the result of the connector in

properties.label: Result expression
properties.description: Expression to map the inbound payload to process variables

name: Amazon SQS Message Start Event Connector

groups.label: Use next attribute names for activation condition
Correlation
groups.tooltip: Learn more about message correlation in the documentation.

groups.label: Deduplication
groups.tooltip: Deduplication allows you to configure multiple inbound connector elements to reuse the same backend (consumer/thread/endpoint) by sharing the same deduplication ID.

properties.label: Authentication
properties.description: Specify AWS authentication strategy. Learn more at the documentation page

properties.label: Access key
properties.description: Provide an IAM access key tailored to a user, equipped with the necessary permissions

properties.label: Secret key
properties.description: Provide a secret key of a user with permissions to invoke specified AWS Lambda function

properties.label: Region
properties.description: Specify the AWS region

properties.label: Endpoint
properties.description: Specify endpoint if need to use custom endpoint

properties.label: Queue URL
properties.description: Specify the URL of the SQS queue where you would like to subscribe to

properties.label: Polling wait time
properties.description: The duration (in seconds) for which the call waits for a message to arrive in the queue before returning. See documentation for details

properties.label: Attribute names
properties.description: Array of queue attribute names. See documentation for details

properties.label: Message attribute names
properties.description: Array of message attribute names. See documentation for details

properties.label: Activation condition
properties.description: Condition under which the Connector triggers. Leave empty to catch all events

properties.label: Consume unmatched events
properties.tooltip: Unmatched events are rejected by default, allowing the upstream service to handle the error. Check this box to consume unmatched events and return a success response

properties.label: Subprocess correlation required
properties.description: Indicates whether correlation is required. This is needed for event-based subprocess message start events

properties.label: Correlation key (process)
properties.description: Sets up the correlation key from process variables

properties.label: Correlation key (payload)
properties.description: Extracts the correlation key from the incoming message payload

properties.label: Message TTL
properties.description: Time-to-live for the message in the broker (ISO-8601 duration)

properties.label: Message ID expression
properties.description: Expression to extract unique identifier of a message

properties.label: Manual mode
properties.description: By default, similar connectors receive the same deduplication ID. Customize by activating manual mode

pattern.message: can only contain alphanumeric characters, dashes, and underscores

properties.label: Result variable
properties.description: Name of variable to store the response in

properties.label: Result expression
properties.description: Expression to map the response into process variables
